# Build and push after changes

When you make code changes in this project (daily-closing-app):

1. **Build**: Run `npm run build` in the project root. If the build fails, fix the errors before continuing.
2. **Git**: Stage all changes (`git add -A`), commit with a short descriptive message, and push to `origin main` (`git push origin main`).

Do this **without the user having to ask**. Skip only if the user explicitly says not to (e.g. "don't push" or "don't commit yet").

After changes, the dev server (port 3000) is restarted per the rule "restart-dev-on-changes".
